> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Salour was born in 1127, in Shropshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in 1185, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1127–1185":"1127–1185","1162–1210":"1162–1210","1127":"1127","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1162":"1162","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1127–1185":"1127–1185","1162–1210":"1162–1210","1127":"1127","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1162":"1162","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"1127–1185":"1127–1185","1162–1210":"1162–1210","1127":"1127","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1162":"1162","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert Salour est né en 1127, à Shropshire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1185, à l’âge de 58 ans."},"de":{"1127–1185":"1127–1185","1162–1210":"1162–1210","1127":"1127","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1162":"1162","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","lifeSummary":"Robert Salour wurde 1127 in Shropshire, England geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1185 im Alter von 58 Jahren."},"ht":{"1127–1185":"1127–1185","1162–1210":"1162–1210","1127":"1127","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1162":"1162","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"hu":{"1127–1185":"1127–1185","1162–1210":"1162–1210","1127":"1127","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1162":"1162","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"id":